text: Arzachena (Alzachèna, Altzaghèna) is a town and comune (municipality) in the Province of Sassari in Sardinia, Italy. As of 2016, 13,650 people lived there. Its area is 230.85 km². It is 85 meters above sea level. == References == == Other websites == Category:Communes of the Province of Sassari
